        PORT ACCURACY
        -------------

        To the best of our knowledge the port is 95% accurate;
        as the original demo heavily relies on a mix of 70 Hz
        vertical blanking synchronization and timing to the music
        replay, there may be subtle differences in timing.



        FUTURE PLANS
        ------------

        Many of you may rightfully be asking if this port can be
        moved to further platforms (Linux, Mac, or something more
        exotic), and the answer is "eventually":

        The original demo, as you may know, is written about 80%
        in assembly, and as such, it's tightly tied to the
        architecture and endianness of x86; moving from DOS to
        Windows was certainly the most obvious and least complicated
        lift. Our goal was to port the demo as accurately as
        possible, with as much of the original code left intact as
        possible, and as such, the current version may not be as
        portable as one would hope.

        However, we plan to continue on this further, and create a
        further generation of the port where we would convert the
        entire demo to a portable language (C), and create a
        "standards compliant" version that would allow for easier
        porting between platforms - we haven't quite started work
        on this yet, but once we reach a certain stage, we plan to
        involve more of the open source community to help us with
        that, so keep an eye and ear out for updates about this!



